TASK-1-PRESENTATION REPORT
I created my digital literacy infographic using Canva, 
where I selected a fun and interactive template that already
included relevant images and design elements. Instead of
designing everything from scratch, I focused on customizing 
the content and arranging the sections in a clear and 
visually appealing way. Canva’s drag-and-drop features and
built-in icons made the process easier and more interesting.
The infographic covers key aspects of digital literacy such 
as understanding digital tools, practicing safe internet 
usage, and being responsible online. I included tools like 
Canva for designing and GitHub for project work and version 
control. Using visuals and icons helped me present the 
information in a more engaging way instead of just plain text.
One challenge I faced was attaching the infographic image in 
VS Code and uploading it to GitHub. It was confusing at first,
especially understanding file paths, but after some effort, 
I was able to figure it out. Overall, this task was both 
creative and technical, and it helped me learn useful skills 
for the future.


TASK-2-PORTFOLIO REPORT
For this task, I created profiles on LinkedIn, GitHub, and Stack 
Overflow, which are commonly used platforms in the tech field. 
LinkedIn helps in building a professional profile and connecting 
with people from different industries. GitHub is mainly used to 
upload and manage coding projects, which is useful for showcasing 
skills. Stack Overflow is helpful for solving doubts, as many 
developers share solutions and explanations there.
Over the next four years, I plan to use these platforms regularly 
to improve my skills and gain more exposure. I will upload my 
projects on GitHub to track my progress and build a strong portfolio. 
On Stack Overflow, I will use it to clear my doubts and try to 
contribute by answering questions once I gain confidence. LinkedIn 
will help me stay updated and connect with professionals for future 
opportunities. Overall, I believe these platforms will be very 
useful for my learning and career growth.
